I guess that with a good bard or by kitting mobs you can even do Fear without chanter.<br>
But 2 is the least you need for a &quot;classic&quot; raid in good condition more can be useful but dont add much (but it help if one chanter dont show or if one need leave early...)<br>
<br>
Elkanir <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#313532><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uphazy.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Phazy</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Adventurer of Underfoot</span><br>  Posts: 49<br> <font color=#CC9900>(5/4/01 5:39:54 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: The Best Team., the Worst team for a Fear raid</span><hr size=1> I personally &quot;like&quot; to see 4 Enchanters on a fear raid. <br>
2 for pull team (seems that the pull enchanter has one of the more dangerous jobs, so adding a second ecnhater to pull as a back up seems to have worked well)Then one in camp for speed and one in camp for Clarity.<br>
<br>
But seems 2 is a standard(one for pull team and one for clarity and speed when mana permits). <br>
<br>
<br>
 <p><center>Phazy Daayz 52st lvl Disciple<center><br><center> EXILE<center></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#414141><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uadunofbrell.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Adun of Brell</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/image/globalBlack.gif BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Burn the Witch! [Mod]</span><br>  Posts: 1863<br> <font color=#CC9900>(5/4/01 7:48:38 am)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://www.pangea.ca/~grinch/ladun.jpg width=67 height=150></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: The Best Team., the Worst team for a Fear raid</span><hr size=1> Depends on the quality of the rest of your crew, and the quality of the chanters you have.<br>
<br>
A 55+ chanter with epic can mostly handle keeping all tanks hasted, &amp; mobs CC's.  I have done fear several times where I played both Adun pulling, &amp; Keigan on primary CC/buffs.  (Anyone out there remember those days?  /shout Okay, you've got 30 seconds to come get clarity, then I'm pulling again <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> )<br>
<br>
Depends on your puller too.  It's possible to pull fear in a manner that doesn't require Chanters at all.  But it sucks to not have clarity/haste.  It's also more work for the puller, and it means you basically need a ranger or a druid to do it.<br>
<br>
If you've got a 54+ chanter that's used to fear, 1 chanter is fine.  A backup chanter to do haste/clarity would be helpful too. <p><img src="http://www.pangea.ca/~grinch/sadune.jpg" width="400" height="175"></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#313532><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uselilya.showPublicProfile?language=EN>selilya</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Winnower of the Harvest</span><br>  Posts: 363<br> <font color=#CC9900>(5/4/01 8:18:47 am)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://members.aol.com/selilya/sel_head.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: The Best Team., the Worst team for a Fear raid</span><hr size=1> Don't forget the other classes can contribute to the traditional enchanter role.  Shaman do all kinds of good things (love that slow!), mages can crank out mod rods if needed, and necro's can do tons of things...mana feeds, Screaming Terror if they have to (limited time mez), nullify magic.  And I know the other casting classes have tasks they contribute as well.<br>
<br>
Happy Hunting in Fear! <p>Selilya Withertouch<BR>
