</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#414141><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ukallikamerov.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Kalli Kamerov</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Protector of Underfoot</span><br>  Posts: 487<br> <font color=#CC9900>(5/5/01 2:08:50 am)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://images.honesty.com/imagedata/h/895/90/28959015.jpg width = 135 height = 184></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: The Best Team., the Worst team for a Fear raid</span><hr size=1> I've done fear as the only enchanter before, and while doable, it's also a real headache constantly having to buff people.<br>
<br>
Basically, as Adune said, the less enchanters you have, the more discretion you have to use while pulling.  If you've got an overabundance of people, levels and / or crowd control, pull them 10 at a time, if you're raid is primarily levels 46-50 and you've only got 2 5 mobs at a time.<br>
<br>
The first time I did it (WoW raid, Thanksgiving '00), I kept a 24 person raid in clarity and augment, had a necro glued to my butt for the whole raid and the pull ranger and druid kiting and pulling in 2-3's sets for mezzing. (I was level 48 so mezzing the more resistant mobs was still a pain).<br>
<br>
Basically, for optimal performance, you want a 54th+ enchanter for Croud control and C2 on the clerics and main buffers one other enchanter for haste &amp; clarity on the tanks and other casters.<br>
<br>
If you've got a larger raid, 30-36 people, you might want to add a 3rd enchanter so that you can use more superior forms of haste, but that's more of a luxury than an essential.<br>
<br>
I guess this post should've just read &quot;what Adune said&quot;. *shrug*<br>
<br>
Kalli Kamerov<br>
55th Enchantress<br>
Poison Arrow <p><img src="http://images.honesty.com/imagedata/h/895/90/28959014.jpg"</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#313532><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/usheebla1.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Sheebla1</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Adventurer of Underfoot</span><br>  Posts: 78<br> <font color=#CC9900>(5/5/01 9:10:23 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: The Best Team., the Worst team for a Fear raid</span><hr size=1> One of the best Fear raids I have ever been on was with only 18 people and no enchanter.  We had to fight for the safe spot on the North wall in the midst of ressing the rest of the raid.  We had a few mobs in camp and we were ressing and joining the fight as fast as we could.  Everyone who had any healing abilities at all were healing.  When one valient warrior dropped, he was immediately ressed and thrown back into the carnage.  We finally gained the upperhand at the safe spot and took control of the area.  The going was very slow.  When we finally did get to the first house, we were asked to go to help an ill fated Naggy raid.  Our plan was to come back after Naggy and finish Fear.<br>
<br>
We went to SolB, the zone went down, then the server went down, but this was a very tight raid, the action was non-stop and intense and the teamwork was inspiring.<br>
<br>
Sheebla <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#414141><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/bbrellserilis.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=kobayashi>Kobayashi</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>The Usual Suspect</span><br>  Posts: 670<br> <font color=#CC9900>(5/5/01 1:11:46 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Hmmm</span><hr size=1> My view is that the best setup for a planar raid is any combination where you have fun!<br>
<br>
1, 2, 20 or 0 enchanters, it doesnt matter, its wether you finish the day with a smile on your face!<br>
<br>
Kobayashi<br>
59th wiz<br>
